The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Cong suicide
                                                                                                               Cong suicide
                            
	Porayar, Feb. 7 (PTI): A Congress worker today allegedly committed suicide by setting himself on fire in Tamil Nadus Nagapattinam district, reportedly demanding a ceasefire between the Tamil Tigers and the government in Sri Lanka.        
	While engulfed in flames, Ravichandran, 47, raised slogans demanding an end to the killing of Tamils in Sri Lanka, police said.                                                                                                                                                                            
